 :tx/rationale "UAQ INSIGHT 7: ADR CRYSTALLIZATION NEEDED. The Universal Acquisition Function needs a formal ADR before implementation. ADR-FOUNDATION-025: Universal Acquisition Function — All recommendation, projection, and measurement decisions unified through A(t,x) = impact * relevance * novelty * confidence. DECISION: Replace AttentionScore with AcquisitionScore. Replace five independent ranking systems with one parameterized function. Extend hypothesis ledger to record item type for per-type calibration. ALTERNATIVES REJECTED: (1) Keep five systems, calibrate independently — rejected because calibration is 5x slower and systems can contradict each other. (2) Merge only R(t) and ACP, keep others separate — rejected because the algebraic insight is that ALL five systems answer the same question. Partial unification loses the compositional property. (3) Design a new system from scratch — rejected because every component already exists, only the composition is missing. FALSIFICATION: The ADR is violated if any recommendation decision requires information not available in the four factors (impact, relevance, novelty, confidence). If such a case exists, a fifth factor is needed. SPEC: ADR-FOUNDATION-019 references the UAQ concept. ADR-FOUNDATION-025 formalizes it."
